   3:WavPlayer.cpp ****  * ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ
   4:WavPlayer.cpp ****  * Target : Daisy Seed (STM32H750) + libDaisy
   5:WavPlayer.cpp ****  * Author : Alex Ikeda
   6:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
   7:WavPlayer.cpp ****  * ŌöĆŌöĆ Hardware connections ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö
   8:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
   9:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Selector mux  (controls which channel mux is enabled)
  10:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *    S0 ŌåÆ D17 | S1 ŌåÆ D16 | S2 ŌåÆ D15
  11:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  12:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Channel muxes (8├Ś, all share the same address lines)
  13:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *    S0 ŌåÆ D20 | S1 ŌåÆ D19 | S2 ŌåÆ D18
  14:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  15:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Analog input  ŌĆö active sensor output ŌåÆ A8
  16:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Audio output  ŌĆö waveform ŌåÆ OUT_L (audio out 1)
ARM GAS  /var/folders/th/s5djnwg15xxc0dk87c413f_h0000gn/T//ccCW3aXI.s 			page 9


  17:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  18:WavPlayer.cpp ****  * ŌöĆŌöĆ Grid addressing (col 0..7, row 0..7) ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ
  19:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  20:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  col_pair     = col / 2
  21:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  channel_base = (col % 2 == 0) ? 4 : 0      even cols use ch 4ŌĆō7, odd use 0ŌĆō3
  22:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  selector     = col_pair * 2 + (row >= 4)    top half ŌåÆ even sel, bottom ŌåÆ odd
  23:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  ch_address   = channel_base + (row % 4)
  24:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  25:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Example:  col=0 row=0 ŌåÆ sel=0 ch=4  (top of col 1, sensor a4, selector a0)
  26:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *            col=0 row=6 ŌåÆ sel=1 ch=6  (bottom of col 1, sensor a6, selector a1)
  27:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *            col=1 row=0 ŌåÆ sel=0 ch=0  (top of col 2, sensor a0, selector a0)
  28:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  29:WavPlayer.cpp ****  * ŌöĆŌöĆ Waveform semantics ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ
  30:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  31:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Per-column positions feed 8 control points: amp0..amp7
  32:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  ZERO_ROW (3.5) is the zero-amplitude reference ŌĆö the midpoint between rows 3
  33:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  and 4.  The mapping is symmetric: p=0 ŌåÆ ŌłÆ1.0, p=3.5 ŌåÆ 0.0, p=7 ŌåÆ +1.0.
  34:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  At idle (no magnet), UpdatePosition holds each column at ZERO_ROW, so all
  35:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  control points remain at 0 and the output is silence.
  36:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Interpolated via Catmull-Rom cubic Hermite ŌåÆ smooth but saw/triangle capable.
  37:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  Wavetable swaps use a short linear crossfade (CROSSFADE_LEN samples) so
  38:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  clicks are eliminated regardless of waveform shape at the swap point.
  39:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  40:WavPlayer.cpp ****  * ŌöĆŌöĆ Noise filtering ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ
  41:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *
  42:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  1. Deviation threshold (kNoiseFloor):       sensor differences (compared to baseline) 
  43:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *                                              below this are ignored.
  44:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  2. Centroid weighting:                      position is the deviation-weighted
  45:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *                                              centroid of all active sensors,
  46:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *                                              giving sub-sensor precision for free.
  47:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  3. Hysteresis dead-zone (kPosDead):         new centroid must differ from current
  48:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *                                              position by > kPosDead to register.
  49:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *  4. Smoothing (kSmooth):                     moving average on position
  50:WavPlayer.cpp ****  *                                              eliminates residual scan-to-scan jitter.
  51:WavPlayer.cpp ****  */
  52:WavPlayer.cpp **** 
  53:WavPlayer.cpp **** 
